Interface EndorsementKeys

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, EndorsementKeysTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EndorsementKeysStub

    public interface EndorsementKeys
extends Service, EndorsementKeysTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The EndorsementKeys interface provides methods to manage Trusted Platform Module (TPM) Endorsement Keys (EK) on a cluster level. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        EndorsementKeys.ListInvocation list(java.lang.String cluster)
        Return a list of configured TPM endorsement keys in a cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        A list of configured endorsement keys.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        InvalidArgument - if the cluster id is empty.
        NotFound - if the cluster is not found.
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The id of the cluster on which the operation will be executed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        Returns:
        instance of EndorsementKeys.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • create

        EndorsementKeys.CreateInvocation create(java.lang.String cluster,
                                        EndorsementKeysTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Add a new TPM endorsement key on a cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Operation Errors:
        AlreadyExists - if the endorsement key name exists.
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        InvalidArgument - if the configuration is invalid or cluster id is empty.
        NotFound - if cluster doesn't match to any cluster in the vCenter.
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The id of the cluster on which the operation will be executed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - The configuration.
        Returns:
        instance of EndorsementKeys.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

        EndorsementKeys.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String cluster,

        Remove a TPM endorsement key on a cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        InvalidArgument - if the name is invalid or cluster id is empty.
        NotFound - if the name is not found or cluster doesn't match to any cluster in the vCenter.
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The id of the cluster on which the operation will be executed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
